        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "As an inconstancy with other view helpers, formRadio doesn't give the radio buttons a unique id.\r\n\r\nI came by this error while using Zend_Form, which depends on this View_Helper class\r\n\r\nZend_Form_Decorator_ViewHelper eventually calls the helper with something like seen below:\r\n{code}\r\nformRadio('subfrm', 'true', array('options' => array('true' => '', 'false' => ''), 'listsep' => ''));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis results in:\r\n{code}\r\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\r\n<input name=\"subfrm\" value=\"true\" checked=\"checked\" type=\"radio\">\r\n<\/label>\r\n<br>\r\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\r\n<input name=\"subfrm\" value=\"false\" type=\"radio\">\r\n<\/label>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nWhile the expected result would be something like:\r\n{code}\r\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\r\n<input name=\"subfrm\" id=\"subfrm-true\" value=\"true\" checked=\"checked\" type=\"radio\">\r\n<\/label>\r\n<br>\r\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\r\n<input name=\"subfrm\" id=\"subfrm-false\" value=\"false\" type=\"radio\">\r\n<\/label>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nA suggested fix would be:\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ Wrap the radios in labels\r\n            $radio = '<label'\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . '>'\r\n                    . (('prepend' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n                    . '<input type=\"' . $this->_inputType . '\"'\r\n                    . ' id=\"' . preg_replace('\/\\[([^\\]]+)\\]\/', '-$1', $name) .'-'. $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"' \/\/add this line\r\n                    . ' name=\"' . $name . '\"'\r\n                    . ' value=\"' . $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\r\n                    . $checked\r\n                    . $disabled\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs) \r\n                    . $endTag\r\n                    . (('append' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n                    . '<\/label>';\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe preg replace is there to also address names with brackets. So subfrm[0] with value true would be converted to subfrm-0-true. It was copied from Zend_Form_Decorator_ViewHelper, so i think it's safe, but didn't create it."
        },
